<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/2959> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #2959" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Killed and his army destroyed in Thessaly by Andriscus the pretender to the throne of Macedon (Liv. Oxy. Per. 50, and Per. 50; Flor. 1.30.4; Eutrop. 4.13; Oros. 4.22.9; Zon. 9.28; cf. Diod. 32.9; Head, HN\n     239, on his coins and those of the victor). See 149, Praetors.{462}" .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/2958> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #2958" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "From Livy (Oxy. Per. 50) it appears that his defeat and death should be dated in 148." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/2940> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #2940" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Opposed Andriscus in Macedonia (Liv. Oxy. Per. and Per. 50; Flor. 1.30.4; Eutrop. 4.13; Oros. 4.22.9; Zon. 9.28; cf. Diod. 32.9; and Head, HN\n     239, on his coins; A.- J. Reinach, Jour. Int. Arch. Num. 15 [1913] 136-139). See 148." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/2939> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #2939" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "The cognomen Thalna, general in his family, is inferred from the punning type of the {Gr} on his coins (see Head, HN\n   \n    2\n   \n   239, and references there)." .
